helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear Team,

We are pleased to invite you to the upcoming *Allergy and Phadiatop Test
Training Session*, organized to strengthen our understanding of allergy
diagnostics and to ensure consistent, accurate communication across all
Thyrocare verticals.

*This session will cover:*

   -

   Basics of allergy and immune response
   -

   Understanding atopy and non-atopic conditions
   -

   Overview and clinical significance of the Phadiatop test

*Session Details:*
*Topic:* Allergy and Phadiatop Test
*Date:* Thursday, 4 December
*Time:* 3:30 PM  4:30 PM
*Join via Google Meet:* https://meet.google.com/pcd-jonp-okd

We look forward to your active participation and engagement in this
important training.


-- 
*Thanks & Regards,*
Learning and Development Team


--

Hi PharmEasy Team,

I am writing to express my strong dissatisfaction with the unprofessional
experience I faced today with your lab test sample collection service
booked on your platform.

I had scheduled lab tests for my parents, and the technician was supposed
to collect the samples between* 7:00 AM and 8:00 AM  this morning *(screenshot
attached).

However, the technician *did not arrive* during the scheduled slot. When I
contacted him, he informed me that his vehicle had a puncture and that he
would reach it in 15 minutes. Despite continuous follow-ups, he kept
repeating that he was coming, but *never turned up*. I also reached out
to your helpdesk, but unfortunately, received no effective support. After
that technician's phone was switched off which is quite irresponsible
behaviour.

My parents had been *fasting for more than 12 hours*, and by *9:30 AM*.
This caused significant inconvenience, frustration, and unnecessary stress,
especially for elderly individuals.

Because of this delay,

   -

   I had to miss my office today,
   -

   My father also got delayed for his work.

After 9:30 AM, your team informed me about rescheduling, but considering
the *time, energy wasted, and stress*, I expect PharmEasy to *compensate
for the inconvenience caused* and ensure strict action against such
negligence.

This experience has severely impacted my trust in PharmEasys reliability,
and I hope you will address this matter urgently and appropriately.

Looking forward to your prompt resolution.

Regards,
Divya Kaku
9824839106

The Art of Successful Negotiation/p>

Tactics to Influence, Align & Close Deals
Effective negotiation is a cornerstone of professional success, enabling you to resolve conflicts, build stronger relationships and achieve outcomes that benefit everyone involved. This dynamic one-day workshop equips participants with essential negotiation techniquesfrom clear communication and empathic listening to recognising shared interests and crafting mutually rewarding solutions. Through interactive role-plays, real-world case examples and hands-on practice, you will refine your ability to manage difficult conversations, navigate disagreements and close agreements with confidence. By the end of the session, youll walk away with practical tools, proven strategies and the self-assurance to negotiate successfully in any personal or professional situation.

Learning Outcomes

By the end of the workshop, you will be equipped with following skills:
  • Apply Effective Communication Strategies: Implement appropriate communication strategies tailored to the negotiation context, ensuring clarity and understanding between all parties involved.
  • Enhance Collaborative Problem-Solving Skills: Develop the ability to engage in collaborative problem-solving, turning potential conflicts into opportunities for mutually beneficial agreements.

  • Classify and Mitigate Cross-Cultural Impacts: Learn to classify cultural differences that may affect negotiations and develop strategies to reduce their impact, fostering smoother interactions across diverse backgrounds.

Today I received Accuchek PERFORMA glucometer strips (100 numbers) which
are intended to be used for the next one+ years. See attached order details.

But the product is 1 year old and expires in 6 months. See attached PRODUCT

Kindly replace this with a newer lot manufactured in the last 1 or 2

failed.

If this product is not replaced or a refund issued, I don't plan to buy
such products from PharmEasy next time.

Novex

This is poor customer service, throwing policy at customers without
understanding the actual issue or showing any interest in improving
customer service.

months?

I have always got a product with 12 to 15 months before expiry from other
online platforms.

I will not buy medicines or products with expiry from pharmeasy. And advise
my friends circle about the same.

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Hi PharmEasy Team,

I am writing to express my strong dissatisfaction with the unprofessional
experience I faced today with your lab test sample collection service
booked on your platform.

I had scheduled lab tests for my parents, and the technician was supposed
to collect the samples between* 7:00 AM and 8:00 AM  this morning.*

However, the technician *did not arrive* during the scheduled slot. When I
contacted him, he informed me that his vehicle had a puncture and that he
would reach it in 15 minutes. Despite continuous follow-ups, he kept
repeating that he was coming, but *never turned up*. I also reached out
to your helpdesk, but unfortunately, received no effective support. After
that technician's phone was switched off which is quite irresponsible
behaviour.

My parents had been *fasting for more than 12 hours*, and by *9:30 AM*.
This caused significant inconvenience, frustration, and unnecessary stress,
especially for elderly individuals.

Because of this delay,

   -

   I had to miss my office today,
   -

   My father also got delayed for his work.

After 9:30 AM, your team informed me about rescheduling, but considering
the *time, energy wasted, and stress*, I expect PharmEasy to *compensate
for the inconvenience caused* and ensure strict action against such
negligence.

This experience has severely impacted my trust in PharmEasys reliability,
and I hope you will address this matter urgently and appropriately.

Looking forward to your prompt resolution.

Regards,
Divya Kaku
9824839106

--
